{"title_page": "Thomas Boberg", "text_new": "{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name         = Thomas Boberg\n| image        = Thomas-boberg_DSC01007.jpg\n| image_size   = 250\n| caption      = Boberg at Literaturexchange Festival in Aarhus, Denmark, 2019\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1960|5|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[Roskilde]], [[Denmark]]\n| occupation   = [[Poet]], [[travel writing|travel writer]]\n| notableworks = ''Americas''; ''Livsstil''\n| website      = \n}}\n\n[[File:Boberg, Thomas -FILSA 2015 11 07 fRF01.jpg|thumb|Boberg at the [[Santiago International Book Fair]], 2015]]\n'''Thomas Boberg''' (born 5 May 1960 in [[Roskilde]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.danishliterature.info/index.php?id=2092&no_cache=1&tx_lfforfatter_pi2%5Bstage%5D=8&tx_lfforfatter_pi2%5Buid%5D=60&tx_lfforfatter_pi2%5Blang%5D=_eng|title=Biography about Thomas Boberg|publisher=Danish Arts Agency|accessdate=2009-10-19}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> is a Danish poet and [[travel writing|travel writer]]. Since his debut in 1984 he has received extensive recognition for his contribution to Danish literature. Since 2018 member of The Danish Academy (Det Danske Akademi).\n\nBoberg lived in [[Peru]] for several years and has traveled widely in Latin America and Africa.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|url=http://snl.no/Thomas_Boberg|title=Thomas Boberg|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref> Many of his works stem from his travels in South and Central America, often focusing on the exploited and poor.<ref name=\"profile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.danishliterature.info/index.php?id=2092&no_cache=1&tx_lfforfatter_pi1%5Buid%5D=60&tx_lfforfatter_pi2%5Blang%5D=_eng|title=Author Profile|last=Conrad|first=Neal Ashley|year=1999|publisher=Danish Arts Agency|accessdate=2009-10-19}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> Boberg has been nominated twice for the [[Nordic Council's Literature Prize]], in 1999 for ''Americas'',<ref name=\"nrk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nrk.no/nyheter/kultur/litteratur/1.3830644|title=P\u00e5 reise med Thomas Boberg|last=Thiis-Evensen|first=Charlotte|date=2007-10-23|publisher=[[NRK]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref> and in 2006 for ''Livsstil'' (''Life Style'').<ref name=\"nordic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nordic-literature.org/2006/english/articles/104.htm|title=Chewing on the devil's throat|last=St\u00f8lan|first=Arne Hugo|publisher=Nordic Literature and Library Committee|accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref>\n\nThomas Boberg is the son of the surrealist painter [[J\u00f8rgen Boberg]] (1940\u20132009).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kristeligt-dagblad.dk/mennesker/rejseeventyrets-digter|title=Rejseeventyrets digter: Den anerkendte danske digter Thomas Boberg har levet det meste af sit voksenliv i udlandet. I dag fylder den berejste forfatter 50 \u00e5r|author=Daniel \u00d8hrstr\u00f8m|newspaper=Kristeligt Dagblad|date=5 July 2010|accessdate=16 November 2014 |language=Danish}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n*''Hv\u00e6sende ved mit \u00f8jekast'' (1984) - poems\n*''Ud af mit liv'' (1985) - poems\n*''Hvid Gl\u00f8d'' (1986) - poems\n*''Slaggerdyret'' (1987) - poems\n*''Vor tids historie'' (1989) - poems\n*''Marionetdr\u00f8mme'' (1991) - poems\n*''Vandb\u00e6rere'' (1993) - poems\n*''Pelikanens Flugt'' (1994) - poems\n*''S\u00f8lvtr\u00e5den'' (1996) - travel memoirs\n*''Under Hundestjernen'' (1997) - poems\n*''Marokkansk Motiv'' (1998) - with [[Simon Lautrop]]\n*''Americas'' (1999) - travel memoirs\n*''En st\u00e5ende aftale'' (2002) - poems\n*''Invitation til at rejse'' (2003) - travel memoirs\n*''Livsstil'' (2005) - poems\n*''Under Uret'' (2006) - short stories\n*''G\u00e6stebogen'' (2007) - poems\n*''Flakker'' (2008) - novel\n* ''Boothill'' (2009) - digte\n* ''Heste\u00e6derne'' (2010) \u2013 digte\n* ''Heste\u00e6derne II'' (2011) \u2013 digte\n* ''I den n\u00e6ste by'' (2012) - rejseminder\n* ''Fantombillede''(2014) -digte\n* ''Svanesang'' (2015) - digte\n* ''Heste\u00e6derne/Trilogien'' (2015) - digte\n* ''Mexicocitydigte'' (2017) - digte\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{commons category}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boberg, Thomas}}\n[[Category:Danish male poets]]\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Grand Prize of the Danish Academy]]\n[[Category:20th-century Danish poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century Danish male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish male writers]]\n\n\n{{Denmark-poet-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name         = Thomas Boberg\n| image        = Thomas-boberg_DSC01007.jpg\n| image_size   = 250\n| caption      = Boberg at Literaturexchange Festival in Aarhus, Denmark, 2019\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1960|5|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[Roskilde]], [[Denmark]]\n| occupation   = [[Poet]], [[travel writing|travel writer]]\n| notableworks = ''Americas''; ''Livsstil''\n| website      = \n}}\n\n[[File:Boberg, Thomas -FILSA 2015 11 07 fRF01.jpg|thumb|Boberg at the [[Santiago International Book Fair]], 2015]]\n'''Thomas Boberg''' (born 5 May 1960 in [[Roskilde]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.danishliterature.info/index.php?id=2092&no_cache=1&tx_lfforfatter_pi2%5Bstage%5D=8&tx_lfforfatter_pi2%5Buid%5D=60&tx_lfforfatter_pi2%5Blang%5D=_eng|title=Biography about Thomas Boberg|publisher=Danish Arts Agency|accessdate=2009-10-19}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> is a Danish poet and [[travel writing|travel writer]]. Since his debut in 1984 he has received extensive recognition for his contribution to Danish literature. Since 2018 member of The Danish Academy (Det Danske Akademi).\n\nBoberg lived in [[Peru]] for several years and has traveled widely in Latin America and Africa.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|url=http://snl.no/Thomas_Boberg|title=Thomas Boberg|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref> Many of his works stem from his travels in South and Central America, often focusing on the exploited and poor.<ref name=\"profile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.danishliterature.info/index.php?id=2092&no_cache=1&tx_lfforfatter_pi1%5Buid%5D=60&tx_lfforfatter_pi2%5Blang%5D=_eng|title=Author Profile|last=Conrad|first=Neal Ashley|year=1999|publisher=Danish Arts Agency|accessdate=2009-10-19}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> Boberg has been nominated twice for the [[Nordic Council's Literature Prize]], in 1999 for ''Americas'',<ref name=\"nrk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nrk.no/nyheter/kultur/litteratur/1.3830644|title=P\u00e5 reise med Thomas Boberg|last=Thiis-Evensen|first=Charlotte|date=2007-10-23|publisher=[[NRK]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref> and in 2006 for ''Livsstil'' (''Life Style'').<ref name=\"nordic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nordic-literature.org/2006/english/articles/104.htm|title=Chewing on the devil's throat|last=St\u00f8lan|first=Arne Hugo|publisher=Nordic Literature and Library Committee|accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref>\n\nThomas Boberg is the son of the surrealist painter [[J\u00f8rgen Boberg]] (1940\u20132009).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kristeligt-dagblad.dk/mennesker/rejseeventyrets-digter|title=Rejseeventyrets digter: Den anerkendte danske digter Thomas Boberg har levet det meste af sit voksenliv i udlandet. I dag fylder den berejste forfatter 50 \u00e5r|author=Daniel \u00d8hrstr\u00f8m|newspaper=Kristeligt Dagblad|date=5 July 2010|accessdate=16 November 2014 |language=Danish}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n*''Hv\u00e6sende ved mit \u00f8jekast'' (1984) - poems\n*''Ud af mit liv'' (1985) - poems\n*''Hvid Gl\u00f8d'' (1986) - poems\n*''Slaggerdyret'' (1987) - poems\n*''Vor tids historie'' (1989) - poems\n*''Marionetdr\u00f8mme'' (1991) - poems\n*''Vandb\u00e6rere'' (1993) - poems\n*''Pelikanens Flugt